# MUTANT: force-h-zero  (domain: emulator-gb)
# ============================================================================
# DEFECT (one): the half-carry flag H is computed as 0 for an AND instruction
# instead of the mandatory H=1. INVARIANTS: "AND: r=a&b; Z N=0 H=1 C=0".
# A great many engines get this wrong by treating AND/OR/XOR uniformly. Here AND
# is forced H=0 (the OR/XOR rule) — a single flipped flag bit.
#
# must_turn_red_gate: emulator-gb trace-diff (per-instruction F field)
# how_the_gate_rejects: the trace-diff compares F line-for-line against the
#   golden/reference. At the line AFTER `AND A` the reference F=0x20 (H=1, bit 5), this
#   mutant emits F=0x00 (H=0). The diff pinpoints the divergence to that exact PC
#   and REJECTS. A gate that only checked A-register values would MISS it (A is
#   correct); only the flag-field diff catches the wrong H.
#
# Same program as golden. The ONLY corrupted line is the post-AND state (L4):
#   reference: A:01 F:20 ... PC:0103   (AND -> H=1, F=0x20; H is bit 5 = 0x20)
#   mutant:    A:01 F:00 ... PC:0103   (AND -> H=0, F=0x00)  <-- INJECTED DEFECT
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
A:01 F:B0 B:00 C:13 D:00 E:D8 H:01 L:4D SP:FFFE PC:0100 PCMEM:3C,3D,A7,18
A:02 F:10 B:00 C:13 D:00 E:D8 H:01 L:4D SP:FFFE PC:0101 PCMEM:3D,A7,18,02
A:01 F:50 B:00 C:13 D:00 E:D8 H:01 L:4D SP:FFFE PC:0102 PCMEM:A7,18,02,00
A:01 F:00 B:00 C:13 D:00 E:D8 H:01 L:4D SP:FFFE PC:0103 PCMEM:18,02,00,00
A:01 F:20 B:00 C:13 D:00 E:D8 H:01 L:4D SP:FFFE PC:0107 PCMEM:00,00,00,00
# diverging_line_index: 3 (0-based) — PC:0103, field F: reference 0x20 vs mutant 0x00
# invariant_violated: AND flag rule (H must be 1). blind_to: A/B/C/D/E/H/L/SP/PC all correct.
